dialogue.text: My oh my, even with the machinations of my home, you were still able to defeat me. Very well, I admit defeat.
You seem to be pretty happy for someone who lost out on two servants, err Shikigami.
Ahahaha, I wasn’t really trying myself.
I was only going at it with a small portion of my talent so I had a feeling that I would've ended up losing.
Besides, if I won, my first order would'’ve been to send you two home so that you can live the rest of your lives happily together.
Beep...
What...
I already have two perfect shikigamis and a darling shrine maiden that I'’m proud to claim as my surrogate daughter.
I truthfully didn’'t need you two... I just wanted to make sure that BF made sure to fight me with his most potential.
Proposing stakes that aren’'t actually there is a small talent of mine...~
Yukari opens up a gap, leading to the same street that BF and GF were at earlier.
Skbeep boop bap beep!
Yeah, we wouldn'’t mind having another match with you and exploring more of Gensokyo. There'’s still so much we have to learn about.
The pleasure would be all mine.
As BF leaves through the gap, GF is about to leave as well before being stopped by\nYukari.
GF. A moment please.
Yes?
There’'s another reason why I whisked you and BF here.
And what would that be?
Please cherish and love BF with all your heart as his life is naturally shorter than yours.
The power that you hold inside of you is very powerful, almost as powerful as my own in some regards.
If you’'re to lose control of your power...… destruction and death would follow in your wake.
I tell you this from my own personal experience. We don’'t need another me in this universe after all.
Promise me that you will heed my warning and love BF with all your heart. Make every moment with him count.
I...… I promise Yukari. I promise not to end up like you, whatever may have happened to you, I won'’t repeat those mistakes.
Hmmm... good.
Now then, go have fun with your love.~
Thanks, I will. It is a Friday Night afterall.~
GF then leaves through the gap before it closes.
A figure in shadows watches the entire week from the back ground on top of a large floating island.
She gives a sigh as she senses the presence of an old friend.
Here to lecture me on eavesdropping again?
Who do you take me for? Kasen?
No, but I take you for an old hag who is quite predicable in what she will say to me.
Do you wish to get hit by a train,\nKiki Setsuko?
I can arrange that for you now if you'd like.
Hahahaha! Relax, I’m only kidding.
Hmm I doubt that, but I digress. Besides, that’s not the reason for my visit today. I’m simply here to ask if you would like to...
go see a concert.
A concert? You mean...?
I do. Get yourself prepared. We'’ll be leaving in a few, and you may want to take that hat off.
We don't want anyone to ask questions.
Kiki, still coated in shadows takes something off of their head, revealing their face as they look down at a worn-down red cap.
